               <head>Miscellaneous works on Sufism, 3 items (a-c)</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85129660">
                  <summary>Miscellaneous collection of three works on Sufism. 
Volume not dated; datable to late seventeenth century. 
Awkward nastaʿlīq. 
Stamped and pencil foliation, original discontinuous Persian foliation. 
Annotations in margins, including collation marks. 
Lacking original binding.
Loose folded paper wrapper (ledger, fragment of Acquittance Roll, dated 19 August 1831, Calcutta); watermarked (initials UEIC, J Whatman Balston &amp; Co, 1828); torn, stained, and incomplete. 
Detached binding of blind tooled brown leather, damaged (Kaithi text exposed along inner edge of broken spine); labels. 
Folios mostly unbound; water and fungal stains, cropped, wormholes, later repairs. 
Condition fragile. 
</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1078-item1">
                     <locus from="1r" to="8v">ff. 1r-8v </locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1078 a. 
</p>
                        <p>Treatise on mystical philosophy by an unnamed author. 
</p>
                        <p>The chronogrammatic title is mentioned in a concluding verse. 
</p>
                        <p>Defective at beginning (starts at folio 25, showing substantial loss). 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end; datable to the late seventeenth century. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21951">Mirʾāt al-maʿānī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_21951">مرآة المعانى</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1078-item2">
                     <locus from="9v" to="63r">ff. 9v-63r</locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100166176979.0x000001 viaf_90042997">Jāmī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_90042997">جامی</persName>
                     </author>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1078 b. </p>
                        <p>Untitled Persian commentary by the celebrated mystic and poet <persName key="viaf_90042997" role="aut">Jāmī</persName> on the <title key="work_21952">Qaṣīdah-yi mīmīyah-yi khumrīyah-yi Fāriẓīyah</title> by the Egyptian mystical poet, <persName key="viaf_118486738" role="ant">Ibn Fāriẓ</persName>, that is, <persName key="viaf_118486738" role="ant">ʿUmar ibn ʿAlī</persName> (d. 632/1235). 
                        </p>
                        <p>The work has been endorsed by a later hand under the conventional title <title key="work_21952">Lavāmiʿ</title>, plural of lāmiʿah, the term used to introduce each new point of analysis. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="3" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1078-item3">
                     <locus from="64r" to="71v">ff. 64r-71v </locus>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21953">Jām-i jahān numā</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_21953">جام جهان نما</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1078 c. </p>
                        <p>Ṣūfī speculative treatise, entitled <title key="work_21953">Jām-i jahān numā</title>, classifying the types and registers of creation, their corresponding phenomenological reality, and encounters with the divine. Authorship has traditionally been attributed to either <persName key="viaf_12221201" role="att">Muḥammad Shīrīn Maghribī</persName> (d, 809/1406-7) or <persName key="viaf_187555132" role="att">Mīr Ghiyās̲ al-Dīn Manṣūr Shīrāzī</persName> (d. 948/1541). 
                        </p>
                        <p>Defective at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Diagrams (ff. 65v, 68v-69r). 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
